(12, 'Insurance', 'Best Progressive Commercial Insurance in USA', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Most businesses have the best progressive commercial insurance policies of their time, but have you researched that? If you are only paying a small percentage of your revenue to a policy and it isnâ€™t providing you with any protection against what your business is facing daily, youâ€™re at risk to lose the value you provide to your customers. Even though you may not have the best commercial insurance, you are not alone.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Having a company with the best progressive commercial insurance is essential, but you need to know why. You need to understand the risks your business faces. Being aware of your business could lead you to find the best corporate policy to protect it. Knowing the type of coverage you need to know can help you make a big difference in your business and the way that your business protects it. You need to cover many risks to your business. The type of coverage that a particular company provides to its clients varies by location. You should also take into account the policy you are paying into. When you own a business, insurance provides both coverage for financial damages as well as protection from potential legal troubles.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial insurance, thatâ€™s the general category under commercial insurance, is a necessary expense for a business. Itâ€™s not really covered in all states, but when you have something going on that is related to the property itself, commercial insurance makes the process of claiming easier.<br>Property insurance and all insurance types should be written for the property as a whole, and not separately for each room, which means you cannot claim for the damage that comes to one room but not the rest. You should also have the fire, theft, and crime insurance that is separate for the whole property because they cover each property differently.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>All types of insurance, like commercial insurance, are necessary for business owners, but to be completely covered, you always need to have general liability coverage as well. Not only for damages made on the property but also if the business owner is held responsible for the personal damages that occur to the business owner. The more business-friendly you are, the more youâ€™re covered in the event of being sued, so thatâ€™s something to note.<br>In order to have an insurance policy, itâ€™s important to read the fine print very carefully. It should match up with your business and what needs to be covered because thatâ€™s how the insurance claim will proceed.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>What is Commercial Business Insurance</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial business insurance covers a broad range of insurance policies meant to protect businesses from risks, such as general liability, commercial property, professional liability, and workersâ€™ compensation. However, depending on their industry, size, and local laws, some companies may need more comprehensive coverage. Commercial business insurance can be purchased separately or in bundles, for example, business ownerâ€™s policies combined general liability and commercial property insurance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Types of Commercial Insurance in the USA</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Property insurance</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Property insurance policies typically cover losses to your business property, which may include buildings and inventory, though they might not cover all of it. Also, you will need to purchase an add-on property policy to cover any other items not covered by the basic policy, including income protection, boiler and machinery insurance, crime insurance, builders risk insurance, tenants insurance, and ordinance or law insurance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Liability</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>A basic liability insurance plan only covers common risks, such as injury to customers on your premises, so you should purchase a more sophisticated form of liability insurance to cover other aspects, such as errors and omissions insurance to cover accidental errors that cause injuries to third parties, and malpractice insurance, also known as professional liability insurance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. Workers Compensation Insurance</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When an employee is injured in the line of duty, this insurance policy pays for the injuries. However hard you may try to protect your workplace, it is hard to control the state of your business completely. For these reasons, purchasing a worker\'s compensation policy is beneficial for your employees since many state laws prohibit them from bringing a negligence case against their employer for injuries related to work.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>4. Commercial Auto Insurance</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial automobile insurance for your business includes trucks, vans, cars, and buses. If your driver hurts someone or your vehicles are damaged or stolen, the coverage will reimburse you depending on the type of vehicle. This insurance plan\'s premiums will depend on the risk of the goods you are moving and your business\'s driving record.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Top 5 Progressive Commercial Insurance in the USA</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.nationwide.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1. Nationwide</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Since business insurance requirements are so diverse, many providers can only provide limited coverage for certain types of ventures. Nationwide stands out from the rest, with policies for both small and large businesses. Nationwide protects just about every type of business: classic policies such as general liability and umbrella insurance added protection from equipment failures and employment-related lawsuits, and even more modern options through cybersecurity protection. One of Nationwide\'s principal challenges is that online quotes are limited to five types of coverage. Almost every industry gets some coverage, though hotels and real estate professionals are among those that donâ€™t receive enough attention. For more detailed insurance information, you will need to call and talk to a customer service representative. In Alaska and Hawaii, Nationwide commercial insurance is not available, although coverage can be obtained anywhere in the continental United States.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.chubb.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2. Chubb</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Chubb is a global insurance company that issues individual and commercial policies worth $40 billion each year and offers a particularly impressive range of business insurance coverages. The Customer General Liability policy is well-suited for small businesses and multinationals alike in more than a thousand industry classification codes. This policy covers pretty much everything, from bodily injury and property damage to litigation and vendors, although global coverage isn\'t included and must be purchased separately, unlike some other policies. The continuum from Chubb can either be added to any general liability policy or purchased individually for companies that need something more tailored. Businesses with annual revenues of less than $30 million can take advantage of Chubbâ€™s business ownerâ€™s policy, which combines general liability with commercial property and other industry-specific types of coverage.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.statefarm.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">3. State Farm</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>State Farm sells more than 100 products, including financial services, banking, and commercial insurance, and AM Best has given it an A++ rating for financial stability. State Farm offers insurance in most states and offers policies for each stage of a company\'s growth cycle, including general liability, professional liability, and other types of coverage that can be added to policies to meet individual needs. State Farm also offers business insurance targeted at certain industries, such as contractors, professional services, caterers, and retailers. State Farm offers discounts for policyholders who combine certain types of coverage, but these discounts vary depending on the types of coverage being combined. These discounts are not available for bundling business coverage. Aside from your business insurance policy, you could also buy homeowners and auto insurance from State Farm and save. Every State Farm agency is independent, so every agent understands small business owners needs because they are business owners.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.travelers.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">4. Travelers</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Travelers is another successful company that has a history that dates back to 1864 when one of its founders started writing accident insurance for two cents. The company is now known as Travelers after the merger of Travelers and St. Paul Companies and is rated A++ by AM Best. Travelers offer insurance solutions for companies in more than 40 industries, including transportation, manufacturing, construction, retail, and public entities. It has however acquired substantial expertise in commercial property insurance. According to the Insurance Information Institute, the company writes so much property insurance that it is projected to be the sixth-largest issuer of commercial property insurance in the United States in 2021. It also writes other types of business insurance, including commercial auto, cyber liability, surety bonds, and workersâ€™ compensation, though prices vary by industry. Because Travelers has offices in the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom, the company is well-positioned to provide insurance for companies doing business internationally.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.nextinsurance.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">5. Next Insurance</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Most commercial insurance policies are designed for companies with multiple employees and high annual revenues, sole proprietors can end up paying sky-high premiums for coverage they don\'t need. Next Insurance is a relatively new player in the commercial insurance market that targets self-employed people who own their businesses. Its policies do not include every type of commercial insurance, but they offer the coverage most important to small businesses: general liability, professional liability, errors and omissions insurance (E&amp;O), commercial auto, tools and equipment, and even workersâ€™ compensation. The company may not be the right choice for all types of businesses, but coverage is widely available in all states. It offers instant online quotes, which is a rarity in business insurance, and it can even start coverage the same day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In conclusion, A variety of risks can be protected by commercial business insurance. Businesses can select from a range of commercial business insurance products, including liability, property or vehicle insurance, and workers\' compensation. Certain businesses may also require specific types of insurance, such as business continuity insurance or business income insurance, after a natural disaster or a cyberattack that could threaten their solvency. In some states, such as New York, New Jersey, and Massachusetts, you are also required to provide short-term disability coverage and paid family leave for employees. Due to the high risk of their work, manufacturers, wholesalers, distributors, importers, and construction firms may require more comprehensive coverage to protect them from legal claims than other businesses.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>1. What are the Expected Costs of Commercial Business Insurance?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The cost of commercial business insurance depends on the company\'s size, location, industry, and the amount of coverage needed. A sole proprietor or small business may pay as little as $20 for basic coverage per month, while a large corporation could face monthly premiums of thousands of dollars or more. Several commercial insurance providers, for example, list annual premiums in their quotes despite presenting all pricing by month.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>2. Does Progressive Offer Pet Insurance?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Progressive offers pet insurance through Pets Best. If you apply for pet insurance, you can save up to 5% on your policy, and you can save an additional 5% if you insure more than one pet. Progressive provides accident, accident and illness, and wellness plans.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>3. Who Needs Commercial General Liability Insurance?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>General liability insurance is the most essential form of business insurance for any business, regardless of its size. A policy protects your business if your business is found to be at fault in an incident and someone is injured on the premises, which is more often than you may think. Commercial liability insurance covers the costs if a claim is brought against your business for bodily injury, property, and advertising damage. Businesses with a higher risk that require more coverage than a general liability policy, for example, general contractors, IT contractors, advertising/marketing, real estate agents, retail shops, restaurants, and more, would have to pay for their defense without general liability insurance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>4. How Much Coverage is Right for My Business?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance, workersâ€™ compensation insurance, cyber liability, commercial property insurance, and general liability insurance are among the many types of insurance available to companies. Itâ€™s important to know that you arenâ€™t over-insuring your business, which could prove to be very expensive, or under-insuring your business, which may prove to be expensive too!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>5. What Does Commercial Business Insurance Typically Include?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Like homeowners insurance, commercial business policies usually contain two main components: property and liability coverage. Property coverage can help keep your business afloat in the event of a covered physical loss, such as a fire in your business. A good policy will protect you in the event of a physical loss of your property, accidents, robbery, and many other events. On the other hand, general liability can help protect your company in the case of a lawsuit and could also provide coverage for bodily injury if someone who is not an employee is injured on your premises or job site. Workers\' compensation, another type of business insurance, is usually insured separately and covers employees who are injured on the job.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '2022-07-24 13:24:21.604401'),
(13, 'Lawyer', 'Best Free Legal Advice For Small Businesses in USA', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>As a small business owner, you may not be able to afford to hire a lawyer at this time. However, claiming that you can\'t afford to hire a lawyer and ignoring the situation is not an option; the consequences are too high.<br>Suppose you\'re in the business of making money. In that case, there are numerous things to keep an eye out for that might land you in court, including intellectual property protection, avoiding lawsuits, and much more.<br>The high expense of employing a lawyer and the potential dangers make it no wonder that many small business owners are interested in finding out if they may get free legal advice. Fortunately, there are several free legal resources where you can receive answers to your queries from experts. You should conduct extensive research to determine the best strategy for you and your business.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Why is Advice From Legal Services So Important in Business?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When a company is just starting, it can be challenging to make sense of the rules and regulations that must be followed. And although company law can be complex, it\'s crucial to get it correctly.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>Here are Five Key Considerations that Should Prompt You to Seek Legal Counsel for Your Company:</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. It will aid in the development of an optimal organisational structure for your business. To a large extent, your tax burden, legal exposure, and operating expenses will depend on the kind of business organisation you select.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. To better understand your legal responsibilities and potential liabilities: As a business owner, you have a duty under the law to know your rights and avoid breaking any rules.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. A conflict with an employee, customer, or supplier may be pretty expensive for a small business, and this tool can help you prevent those costs. With the help of a lawyer, you can settle these disagreements out of court and save yourself trouble and money.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. Try to save money by avoiding the inclusion of illegal or unenforceable clauses; you should consult a good legal counsel before drafting any significant contracts or agreements.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>5. You are more likely to break the law if you don\'t understand how it pertains to your organisation. Therefore, it\'s essential to educate yourself on the subject. Having legal representation can help you avoid getting into trouble with the law and facing potential consequences like fines and jail time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Ways to Get Free Legal Advice</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Take Advantage of Free Legal Clinics and Seminars</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>State bar associations, which issue licences to attorneys and oversee their practice, typically mandate annual pro bono or free legal services hours for their members. Participation in pro bono legal clinics and workshops is one option for lawyers to meet these standards. Many groups offer pro bono legal services, including:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1.  Public institutions like libraries, nonprofits, and courts frequently host free legal aid clinics. At these gatherings, attorneys willing to help out in exchange for attendance attend and offer rudimentary legal guidance. Remember that these attorneys cannot act as your advocates, but they may be able to help you with some initial inquiries in a brief consultation (usually half-hour sessions).</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. Legal aid hotlines are a standard service provided by state bar organisations. The New York City Bar, for instance, offers a free legal advice hotline for low-income New Yorkers to call for help with various issues, including those related to starting and running a business.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. Essential legal advice can also be obtained via law school clinics staffed by students and faculty. Legal clinics at several schools cater to business owners and startups.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Appointments at free legal aid clinics tend to fill up quickly, so plan. Inquiring at local law schools about such clinics is another option.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Make Use of no-cost Consultations</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Many attorneys provide free initial consultations to fulfil their state bar\'s pro bono hour requirements. You can learn if the attorney is a suitable fit for you and your company by asking basic questions and getting some answers during the meeting.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>During your initial session with the attorney, consider asking the following:</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. Where did you grow up? How familiar are you with the issues facing businesses in my field?</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. To what extent will you be involved in my case?</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. \"Will my case possibly necessitate litigation/court appearances?\"</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. How many will other people (legal assistants, partners) be working on my case with you?</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>5. When will we talk about my case, and how will we talk about it (phone, email, in-person appointments)?</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>6. What are your rates?</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In some cases, the initial consultation is all it takes to figure out how to fix your legal issue. However, the talk is usually just the beginning of working with an attorney, and more consultations (at the attorney\'s regular hourly rate) will likely be necessary.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. Look for a Lawyer Who Will Work on a Contingency Basis</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>If you own a small business, you may be surprised to learn that many lawyers are willing to work with you on alternative payment plans. Business lawyers can opt for a contingency fee structure or alternatives to the traditional hourly rate.<br>In a contingency fee arrangement, payment to the attorney is required only in the event of a successful outcome of the case. The attorney\'s fee will reduce the sum granted to you. There is no downside to this payment plan for hiring an attorney, so it\'s essentially the same as getting legal counsel for free.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Although contingency fees are most commonly associated with personal injury cases, they are applicable to many types of litigation, including commercial disputes. Find a firm that will work for you on a contingency fee if your company has been sued and you need legal representation. A contingency fee arrangement is advantageous because it encourages your lawyer to perform their best for you in exchange for payment.<br>Suppose you need the services of a firm that accepts cases on a contingency basis in your area. In that case, you may contact your local bar association for a referral or conduct an online search for \"[your city] + business + contingency fee.\"<br>Fixed-fee and task-based pricing structures are still uncommon in large law firms, but you may find them acceptable in smaller ones willing to work with you on a case-by-case basis. For instance, they may offer a flat rate for analysing contracts instead of hourly billing.<br>Legal marketplaces like these are an excellent way to obtain low-cost or free legal help.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>4. Make Use of a Virtual Legal Aid Provider</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Numerous websites now provide legal advice for free or at a minimal flat charge. Finding legal forms, guidance on company entity formation and referrals to local attorneys are all things that may be accomplished with their help.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>A few of the best services out there are as follows:</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. LegalZoom- It provides custom legal forms, document review, business creation, and unlimited phone calls with a lawyer.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. Rocket Lawyer- It also provides custom legal forms, document inspection, online legal Q&amp;A, business formation, and phone calls with a lawyer.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. LegalShield- You pay a flat monthly fee and get unlimited access to a lawyer via email, phone, and in-person meetings.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. Nolo- It is a free legal article covering various issues written by practising attorneys.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>These online legal marketplaces are an excellent resource for those looking for free or low-cost legal representation.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>5. Legally-Free Software Options</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>There are various paths to securing legal aid through these programmes. For some, access is restricted to those with modest means.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. Legal Services Corporation- Seek out low-cost legal representation in your area.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. LawHelp.org- You can access free local legal aid and answers to your legal issues. These programmes cater to free lawyers for low-income families.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. Law Help Interactive - This tool provides free assistance in completing legal documents, including those for:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Divorce with no legal battles</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Theft of a Person\'s Identified Information</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Legal Entitlement to Visitation</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Evictions and other landlord-tenant disagreements</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. American Bar Association- It allows persons with limited means to get their legal questions answered by a lawyer online. In regards to criminal questions, they refuse to respond.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>5. Directory of Law School Pro Bono Programs- Many schools of law offer official pro bono services, and this directory list them all. Try looking for free legal lawyers near you.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Does a Lawyer for Startups Do?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>A startup lawyer guides business owners through the myriad of legal hoops that must be jumped through before launching and growing a business. Examples of this assistance include helping a startup register as a business in their state, producing the first set of documentation the company may use with its customers and staff, and assisting in negotiating, creating, and modifying investment contracts. Intellectual property, compliance with state and federal regulations, and the writing of employment contracts are all areas in which startup lawyers excel.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Legal Advice for Business Startups</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. Choose your company name with care! It may seem obvious, but it is a typical oversight to choose a name already taken. Internet and social media searches, as well as a visit to Companies House (in the UK) and possibly the UK Intellectual Property Office (IPO) to see if the name is already registered as a trade mark, are all excellent places to start your search.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. If you are a co-founder, you must consider dividing the equity and the work. Use documents like agreements and director service agreements to set everything up as formally as possible. In the long term, investors will be more interested in funding a well-managed startup with detailed records that accept responsibility for its actions.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. Be sure to guard your company\'s name and intellectual property. Buying domain names that include your business name and forming a limited liability corporation are two ways to safeguard your brand once you\'ve settled on a name. It\'s possible to file for a patent or design right if you\'ve invented or developed some cutting-edge innovation or a novel aesthetic.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. You must have written agreements in place with both your clients and your vendors. The revenue-generating client contract is the most vital to your company\'s success. The contract, be it a licence, terms and conditions, or user terms, must be fair to both parties and safeguard your organisation. Suppose your suppliers are developing, designing, providing, or manufacturing something for you. In that case, it\'s in everyone\'s best interest to have a contract outlining the scope of the work, the expected timeline for completion, and who will hold the intellectual property.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>5. Hire a competent attorney and accountant. Having qualified advisors is essential for successful businesses. Advisors who are familiar with your industry and willing to work with you on price and other terms are a dream come true for entrepreneurs and new ventures.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Free Legal Advice Hotline</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Call the toll-free Free Legal Advice Hotline at any time (24/7) at 646 666 9601, and you will be in touch with a local attorney who is familiar with the laws in your state and ready to hear your case. You can get free legal help seven days a week, whenever you need it.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>You can still acquire the professional legal counsel your company needs, even if money is tight. From in-person clinics to online tutorials, those needing legal guidance can access a wealth of resources at no cost. With so many options, you will have all the small business legal support you need to take your business to the next level.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>1. Is it Possible to Acquire Free Legal Counsel for Half an Hour?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Some attorneys offer free initial consultations lasting 30 minutes. To help you budget for the cost of the guidance, some consultants charge a flat rate.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>2. Should I See a Lawyer Before Launching a Small Business?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>One of the best things you can do before launching a business is consult with a small business attorney.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>3. What is a Pro Bono Lawyer?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>As used in the legal field, \"Pro Bono\" means providing legal services to those in need at no cost or a much-reduced rate.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>4. Who is Eligible for Legal Help?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Legal aid is available to those who are low-income or get government assistance based on their financial situation.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>5. How Reliable is LegalZoom as a Resource?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Good.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '2022-07-24 13:29:54.823456');
