(16, 'Loans', 'Best Debt Consolidation Companies For Bad Credit in USA', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>It is possible to consolidate multiple unsecured debts into one manageable instalment loan with a debt consolidation loan. After consolidation, you\'ll make only one payment per month to your new lender rather than several payments to several companies for your various loans and credit cards.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Additionally, a consolidation loan may help your credit rating while saving money. Reducing your credit utilisation ratio by paying off your revolving obligations with an instalment loan may help your credit score.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Kinds of Debt Consolidation Loan</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Secured Debt Consolidation Loans</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Secured loans function similarly to unsecured ones, with the vital distinction being that the borrower is required to pledge an item (often property or car) as \"collateral\" or \"security\" for the loan. That asset is now subject to the lender\'s claim on the non-payment of the debt.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Unsecured Debt Consolidation Loans</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Also known as a personal loan, this type of borrowing involves acquiring additional credit to settle existing debts without pledging any collateral in return for the loan\'s funding. A wide range of interest rates is available depending on your credit score. There is a strong correlation between a borrower\'s credit history and the interest rate they are offered.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Where Will You Get a Debt Consolidation Loan With Bad Credit?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When you have terrible credit, getting a loan from a traditional lender like a bank might be challenging for debt consolidation. Yet, there are still financial institutions that might be willing to give you a chance despite your bad credit.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Online Lenders</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>It\'s possible to find debt consolidation loans with more forgiving terms through online lenders. However, bad credit debt consolidation loans can come with higher interest rates and even fees because of the higher risk involved. It\'s possible that consolidating your debt won\'t help you save money if the interest rate you qualify for is high enough.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Credit Unions</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Credit unions are another option to look into if you have bad credit yet need to consolidate debt. In contrast to banks, credit unions are more likely to approve borrowers with less-than-perfect credit; nonetheless, membership is required. Nevertheless, you may need to look about it before discovering a local credit union or an online credit union ready to deal with your circumstance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>How to Select the Best Debt Consolidation Loan for Bad Credit?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Make sure you look at all these aspects when settling a debt consolidation loan.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Annual Percentage Rates</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Once all fees and interest are factored in, the APR accurately reflects the total yearly cost of the loan. A person\'s interest rate will differ depending on their income, debt, and credit history. Compare several loans by looking at their annual percentage rates. Find a plan with manageable monthly payments and a low-interest rate.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Origination Fees</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>For the trouble of handling your loan, some financial institutions will charge you an origination fee. The one-time fee is usually between 1 and 10 per cent of the loan amount and can be subtracted from the money you get or added to the principal. For this reason, if the charge is to be taken from the loan proceeds, the amount requested must be greater than the total amount of the debts to be paid. If you\'re trying to save money, you should avoid loans that charge this fee unless the annual percentage rate (APR) is lower than what you\'d pay for a loan without the cost.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. Lender Features</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Direct payment to creditors is one consumer-friendly option offered by some lenders. You should also compare the terms of different plans for free credit monitoring and hardship programmes that temporarily lower or halt monthly payments in the event of a financial setback, such as the loss of a job.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>How to Fit for a Debt Consolidation Loan?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Below are the factors for qualifying for a debt consolidation loan.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Your Credit Score</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Debt consolidation lenders want firm credit. Fair-credit customers will pay a higher interest rate than good-credit customers. With exceptional credit, you could get the lowest consolidation loan rate. Bad credit debt consolidation loans may have a minimal credit score and income requirements.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Your Income</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Lenders will assess your debt-to-income ratio and minimum annual income. DTI ratio is the percentage of gross monthly income used to pay debts. A lower ratio demonstrates lenders you can balance income and debt and repay what you owe. Some debt consolidation loan businesses accept DTI ratios as high as 50%, indicating that your monthly debt obligations shouldn\'t exceed half of your monthly income.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. Your Credit History</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bankruptcies, tax liens, repossessions, and foreclosures turn off most lenders. A co-signer or joint application can minimise a lender\'s risk and help you receive a loan. Use a co-signer with caution. Defaulting can harm your relationship and co-credit.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Best Debt Consolidation Companies for Bad Credit?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.firstmidwest.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1. First Midwest Bank</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>First, Midwest offers cheap APRs and few costs. Even with the $150 fee, rates can be as low as 5.23 per cent and won\'t surpass 12.99 per cent. First Midwest Bank is merging with Indiana-based Old National Bank in 2022. It has 250 branches in four states.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The bank\'s APR ranges from 5.23 to 12.99 per cent, with no costs. No upfront or late fees. The $150 paperwork charge will be added to the APR. First Midwest offers $5,000 to $35,000 loans with periods up to seven years. 24-hour funding is available.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>First Midwest is a certified personal loan lender on LendingTree, where it has 4.9/5 stars from over 4,000 reviews. Outstanding fees, closing expenses, and customer service. Some borrowers won\'t qualify. All applicants must have a credit history of at least five years and can apply online or in person.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.upgrade.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2. Upgrade</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>San Francisco\'s Upgrade services loans for Cross River Bank and Blue Ridge Bank. Upgrade\'s online method includes a rate quotation that won\'t affect your credit, a quick application, and funding in one business day. Creditors can also receive funds.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>While Upgrade permits co-signers and joint applicants, consumers with credit scores as low as 550 may qualify. Origination fees of up to 8% may be deducted from loan proceeds. You\'ll need to borrow 8% more than you want. APRs start at 5.94% and range up to 35.97%, with the lowest rates necessitating autopay and direct payments to creditors.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Other advantages include loans from $1,000 to $50,000, no prepayment fee, and the flexibility to adjust your payment due date. Upgrade has excellent evaluations on Trustpilot, with many customers praising its straightforward application and fast payment.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Upgrade loans are unavailable to residents of Washington, DC, Connecticut, Colorado, Iowa, Maryland, Massachusetts, Vermont, or West Virginia</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.freedomplus.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">3. FreedomPlus</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>FreedomPlus offers personal loans sponsored by Cross River Bank or MetaBank. The lender provides loan terms (two to five years) and loan amounts ($7,500 to $40,000). These features make it easy to consolidate debt, spread payments out, and reduce monthly payments.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>FreedomPlus allows direct payment to creditors, like other top picks. Paying 85% of the loan amount toward debt consolidation increases loan eligibility. Origination fees of 1.99% to 4.99% of the loan amount might further increase costs. Before signing up for FreedomPlus, do the arithmetic.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>FreedomPlus personal loans require a 620-credit-score minimum. However, it will not lend more than 35% of a borrower\'s annual income to prospective borrowers. It permits co-signers and co-applicants; 30% of borrowers have joint loans.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>FreedomPlus loans can be utilised for home improvements, weddings, travel, medical, moving, and debt consolidation. You could get a loan the same day you apply. You could get funding in 48 hours</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.lendingclub.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">4. LendingClub</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>LendingClub is the largest online lending platform for personal loans and a peer-to-peer lender. Since its inception in 2007, the platform has issued loans in all states except Iowa, served over 3 million consumers, and provided funding for around $55 billion in loans. You won\'t have to worry about the practicalities of debt consolidation because LendingClub will pay your creditors directly. However, its funding time is not the quickest.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Borrowers can access funds between $1,000 to $40,000, making it possible to consolidate or eliminate significant debt. However, LendingClub\'s annual percentage rates (APRs) are higher than those of competing financial institutions (a maximum of 35.89 per cent). The company only offers loans with maturities of three or five years. In light of this, if you can get better rates elsewhere, you may want to look elsewhere besides LendingClub when considering debt consolidation loans. Borrowers are charged an origination fee of 2% - 6% of the loan amount. Therefore this must be factored into calculating potential savings from loan consolidation.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>An applicant for a personal loan through LendingClub must have a minimum credit score of 600 and a credit history of more than two years. We also verified that the applicant\'s total unsecured debt should not exceed 35% of their gross monthly income (for individuals) or 40% (for couples). LendingClub\'s investor platform considers several indicators, such as income verification, when deciding to lend money. If you and the borrower share a residence, you may apply for the loan, but a co-signer is not permissible.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Debt consolidation is only one personal financial need that can be met with a personal loan from LendingClub. Through its direct payment to third-party lenders, LendingClub further simplifies customer debt consolidation. LendingClub follows the practice of many other lenders by prohibiting its customers from using loaned money for things like paying for college, making large gambling bets, or buying illegal goods and services.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Within four business days of loan approval, LendingClub borrowers can expect to get their cash. This time frame, however, is subject to change depending on the status of the application and any further paperwork or verification that the lender may demand.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.firsttechfed.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">5. First Tech Federal Credit Union</a></strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Since its inception in 1952, First Tech Federal Credit Union has expanded to eight states across the United States. A personal loan is helpful for debt consolidation, and the credit union serves all 50 states.<br>First Tech offers unsecured loans with variable terms from 24 to 84 months, minimum loan amounts as low as $500 and maximum loan amounts as high as $50,000. Applying online is quick and easy to get a personal loan from First Tech Credit Union. If you are authorised, you might get your money as soon as the next working day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The maximum annual percentage rate is 18%, which is modest (credit unions are capped at this rate). First Tech allows you to postpone your first payment for 45 days without charging you an origination or administration fee. Interest on loans may accrue during this time, so borrowers should plan accordingly.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Pre-qualification and a rate quote from First Tech don\'t affect applicants\' credit scores in any way, but the company doesn\'t come clean about its credit requirements either. Application forms are now being accepted online.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Overall, these are the best debt consolidation companies for bad credit. The purpose of any personal loan for debt consolidation should be well defined before the application is made. When choosing if the loan is right for you, consider the rates, fees, and monthly instalments.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>1. Can a Person with a Credit Score of 580 Get a Debt Consolidation Loan?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Yes.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>2. What is the Minimum Credit Score Required to Qualify?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>580 to 680</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>3. Why Have I Been Denied a Loan to Consolidate My Debt?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Three main reasons borrowers are denied a consolidation loan are insufficient income, excessive debt, and poor credit.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>4. Can I Consolidate My Debt With Upstart?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>An Upstart debt consolidation loan allows you to consolidate your unsecured debts into one low monthly payment instead of having multiple accounts with varying interest rates.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>5. Does Upstart Always Confirm Income?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Yes.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '2022-07-24 13:35:54.684443'),
(17, 'Insurance', 'Best Commercial Auto Insurance in USA', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance, often known as business or commercial vehicle insurance, covers automobiles used in a business setting.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance is similar to private auto insurance in that it protects against financial loss but is designed for vehicles used in a corporate environment. Different rules apply to trucks, cement mixers, and trailers to accommodate the wide variety of commercial vehicles on the road today.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance is recommended if you regularly use your car for business purposes or if your company owns a fleet of vehicles. Commercial auto insurance is utilized by business people in all fields, from construction to pizza delivery, because personal auto policies do not extend to commercial cars.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Including coverage, criteria, and pricing, this article will explain the fundamentals of commercial auto insurance. This article will also help you pick the best auto insurance policy for your needs, whether you need protection for a fleet of taxis, construction vehicles, or just your car for frequent business trips.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>How to Qualify for Commercial Auto Insurance?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Liability insurance, which covers medical expenses and repairs to other people\'s vehicles, is required by law in most jurisdictions. While the specifics of commercial auto insurance regulations may vary by state, in most cases, businesses are expected to provide at least the same level of coverage as private motorists.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The state of California mandates that all licenced drivers carry liability insurance with limits of at least $15,000 per person injured or killed, $30,000 per accident, and $5,000 for each incident involving property damage. Proof of insurance must be carried out and made available to law authorities upon request.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>New York has some of the strictest insurance minimums in the country. It also has more stringent minimum limits for liability coverage on auto insurance policies. Individual limits must be at least $25,000, with limitations of $50,000 for numerous injuries, $100,000 for multiple deaths, and $10,000 for property damage for each driver. No-fault and uninsured motorist coverage are both mandatory in the state of New York for drivers.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>What Does Commercial Auto Insurance Cover?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance covers many costs caused by many different things. This section goes over the details of commercial auto insurance coverage.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Different Kinds of Cars and Trucks</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>As we\'ve already discussed, commercial auto insurance policies can cover personal and business vehicles and different types of vehicles standard in other industries. These include passenger cars, vans, pickups, SUVs, cement mixers, hauliers, cranes, various trucks, delivery vans, tractor-trailers, flatbeds, and many more. Commercial truck insurance is a commercial auto insurance policy made just for trucks.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Liability for Injuries to People</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>A crucial part of commercial auto insurance is coverage for bodily injury liability. It pays for the costs of other people getting hurt in an accident where an employee or another covered driver was at fault. Some covered costs would be medical and rehabilitation costs, lost wages, legal fees, and even funeral costs if the accident was fatal. In California and New York, you must pay $30,000 and $50,000 for bodily liability. Most commercial auto insurance policies have much higher limits. Also, it\'s important to remember that the quoted limitations for liability policies apply to each vehicle on the policy.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. Liability for Damage to Property</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Property damage liability insurance supports damages to other people\'s property that a covered driver causes. If you damage someone else\'s vehicle or property, this part of the policy will pay to fix or replace the damage. Buildings, cars, fences, mailboxes, landscaping, and other things could be among the damaged property.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Most states require property damage liability coverage, but the limits are lesser than those for bodily injury liability. The required coverage limit in California and New York is $5,000 and $10,000, respectively. These amounts are just a tiny part of the requirements for bodily injury liability. Most states require both property damage liability and bodily injury liability coverage, so they are often bundled together into one liability insurance package for vehicles.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>4. Damage to the Body</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Physical damage coverage pays to fix or replace the policyholder\'s cars and other property after an event covered by the policy. Many subcategories of bodily damage coverage describe the kinds of accidents and damages covered.<br>There are different kinds of physical damage coverage. Collision coverage pays for damage caused by a crash or roll. Comprehensive insurance pays for damage that isn\'t caused by a collision, like theft, fire, bad weather, or vandalism. Fire and Theft and Combined Additional Coverage are usually for large trucks and construction vehicles. It is a limited comprehensive coverage version covering a smaller range of incidents.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Physical damage coverage only pays for damage to the policyholder\'s cars, so most states don\'t require it. But it is a valuable part of any auto insurance policy because it helps avoid the high costs of fixing or replacing a car after an accident or theft.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>5. Medical Payments</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Medical payments coverage pays for medical bills if an accident hurts the policyholder, company employee, or a covered vehicle passenger. Some parts that are covered are medical bills, lost wages, and even funeral costs. Most states don\'t require this kind of insurance, but it\'s a must if you don\'t want to pay a lot of medical bills after a severe accident that is covered.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>After an accident, the insured person\'s health insurance may or may not pay their medical bills. Even if the person hurt was at fault for the accident, medical payments coverage will always be helpful.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>6. Personal Injury Protection (PIP)</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Personal injury protection (PIP) pays for medical bills if the policyholder, an employee of the business, or a passenger gets hurt in a crash covered by the policy. After an accident, medical payments coverage only pays for medical bills, but PIP coverage pays for both medical bills and loses money for the insured and passengers. PIP coverage will pay for personal injury costs, even if the accident was the insured\'s fault or the fault of a third party.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In some \"no-fault states,\" like Delaware, New Jersey, North Dakota, New York, Florida, Kansas, Kentucky, Hawaii, Pennsylvania, Utah, Michigan, Massachusetts, Minnesota, Oregon, and Texas, PIP insurance is required.<br>Most of the time, PIP is only available in \"no-fault\" states, and most, if not all, insurers won\'t let businesses have both PIP and medical payments coverage simultaneously.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>7. Uninsured Motorist</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Uninsured motorist insurance covers the costs of injuries to the policyholder, an employee, or a passenger who doesn\'t have insurance. After an injury, the at-fault driver\'s insurance will pay for everyone\'s medical bills and property damage. The coverage will pay for the damage and medical bills if the driver who caused the crash does not possess insurance.<br>Even though liability insurance is needed in most states, about one out of every eight drivers doesn\'t have it, as per the National Association of Insurance Commissioners (NAIC). It means there is a high risk of accidents with uninsured drivers.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>Cost of Commercial Auto Insurance</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance premiums are very different and depend on many things. There are a lot of differences, but most small businesses will pay less than $2,500 per vehicle per year.<br>Several things could affect your premium, such as:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. Auto\' makes, models, and ages</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. Cost of the auto</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. Usefulness of the auto</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. Driving record</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>5. History of claims</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>6. Limits of coverage and deductibles</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Many businesses should have at least $500,000 to $1 million in commercial auto liability. A commercial umbrella policy may be a good idea to give your business strong protection to add to this liability.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Best Commercial Auto Insurance Companies in the USA</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Progressive</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When it comes to ensuring trucks, vans, and other commercial vehicles, Progressive Commercial is a great choice. Both AM Best and Standard &amp; Poor\'s have given Progressive high marks; the former gives it an A+ grade, the latter an A.A. Progressive offers a wide range of discounts and perks, as well as coverage that may be tailored to your needs for cars, trucks, and trailers.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Progressive also provides a service called Snapshot ProView, which encourages safe driving by rewarding policyholders who demonstrate this behaviour with lower premiums. Free fleet management tools are available to companies with three or more vehicles.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Liberty Mutual</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Liberty Mutual is the second-largest insurance company in the United States.<br>It is a top property and casualty insurer, with an A rating from both AM Best and Standard &amp; Poor. According to a J.D. Power study of small business clients who purchased commercial products, Liberty Mutual is above the industry average in customer satisfaction.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>As one of the many perks it offers its commercial clients, Liberty Mutual\'s risk control services may help ensure the safety of its drivers. With telematics data, larger fleets can keep tabs on their drivers\' routines. Liberty Mutual also has a mobile app for submitting images of vehicle damage and receiving an insurance quote.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. The Hartford</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The Hartford is a highly well-liked commercial insurer, with an A+ rating from both AM Best and Standard &amp; Poor. The Hartford may provide your business with services like analyzing your company\'s driving records and making recommendations to boost safety. The Hartford\'s FleetAhead programme will help you find the root causes of accidents and reduce your premiums if you use telematics technology.<br>The Hartford\'s commercial insurance is sold through a network of agents and brokers and features online claim reporting.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>4. Geico</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Geico has the cheapest commercial auto insurance. Both Standard &amp; Poor\'s and AM Best have given it high marks for its financial stability, giving it a grade of AA+ and a grade of A++, respectively. The parent firm of this insurance provider came in at number two in J.D. Power\'s most recent study of large commercial insurers for customer satisfaction and number thirteen in their 2020 survey of U.S. vehicle insurance claim satisfaction.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Auto insurance prices and policy access are available quickly and easily online with Geico. Fleets of any size can have policies tailored to their needs, and the vast majority of vehicles are covered (including cars, vans, and trucks, but not semis or tractor-trailers).</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Geico provides combined single limits for liability coverage and the other coverage levels typically available in auto insurance policies. This policy offers the same coverage for an occurrence, regardless of injuries or property damage. Rather than having separate limits (maximum amounts of money the insurer would pay for a single claim) for bodily injury and property damage claims.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>5. Auto-Owners Insurance</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>AM Best has given Auto-Owners Insurance their highest possible grade of A++ for financial stability. The company has a good recognition for customer service and was ranked third in the nation for auto insurance claim satisfaction in J.D. Power\'s 2020 survey.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Remember that Auto-Owners Insurance is only sold in 26 of the 50 states. You\'ll have to contact an independent agent if you want a quote from Auto-Owners. Auto owner\'s insurance coverage automatically covers newly purchased vehicles. Coverage for breakdowns, gaps in a loan or lease, and more are available through various policies.<br>Discounts are available from Auto-Owners Insurance for things like having numerous policies with the company, paying your premiums in total, and having your fleet monitored by telematics. There are seasonal price reductions for farm vehicles as well.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance is the first measure in defending your organization from unexpected charges and losses. Every company is unique and is vulnerable to a variety of distinct hazards. Insurance is not a versatile solution. Talk to insurance specialists before you acquire plans.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>1. Does the Law Require Business Auto Insurance?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Yes.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>2. Is Business Car Insurance Less Expensive than Personal Car Insurance?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>No.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>3. Who is the Biggest Auto Insurance Company for Businesses?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Progressive</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>4. How Much Does Insurance for a Commercial Auto Cost?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Commercial auto insurance is usually between $800 and $1,200 per vehicle annually.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>5. Does Commercial Auto Insurance Cover Vehicles Owned by Employees?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>No.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '2022-07-24 13:40:10.306792');
