r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Here are some best and most popular cosmetic dentists in New York:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>1. Dr. Elisa Mello</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Dr. Elisa Mello, best known for her extraordinary dentistry, is highly regarded for her keen eye for detail and precision, and her patients describe her as the \"dentist with a heart of gold\" because she makes sure patients are well-audited and receive the best smile makeover they can be proud of. Mello was elected to the prestigious Omicron Kappa Upsilon, The National Dental Honor Society which honors academic and clinical excellence in dentistry. She was selected as the senior student with the greatest skill and knowledge in the field of periodontics and given the Samuel Charles Miller Award in Periodontics.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>2. Dr. Lana Rozenberg</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Dr. Lana Rozenberg and her world-famous Manhattan dental practice are truly the epitome of excellence. They offer a rare balance of comfort and quality, which is why they are known as the best dentist in New York. Patients throughout the country, including top A-List celebrities, count on Dr. Rozenberg if they turn to Google for the â€œbest dentist near meâ€. Dr. Lana stands out not only in her mastery in both areas but also in her approach to patients. With an increasing number of people feeling nervous about visiting a dentist, Dr. Lana has decided to make comfort and quality of care as important as excellence.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3><strong>3. Dr. Andrew Flores</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Dr. Andrew Flores is a native of Poughkeepsie, New York. He has been practicing general dentistry since graduating from the NYU School of Dentistry in 2011. Dr. Flores, who was already in private practice, continued his education at the Dawson Academy and Kois Center after graduation for a General Practice Residency at Montefiore Medical Center to improve his dental knowledge. Dr. Flores\'s objective is to provide personal and thorough care, and he respects each person\'s ability to promote and maintain their health.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In conclusion, cosmetic dentistry is a very important and specialized field of dentistry that deals with the improvement of the appearance of the teeth and gums. Dentists in most cases use cosmetic dentistry to address the aesthetics of either their patientsâ€™ teeth or the entire mouth. The best cosmetic dentistry in the US is becoming a very sought-after field of dentistry where patients are finding that they can get a bright, white smile for the whole life of their teeth. This is an ideal investment in their career as their smiles will give them the extra confidence to do things that they might have kept hidden. Get yourself the best dentist in the area listed in the USA and have a nice time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>1. What Kind of Problems Can Cosmetic Dentistry Solve?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Modern cosmetic dentistry improves the appearance of your teeth and has many benefits to your oral health. It is well known that replacing missing teeth with dental implants prevents bone loss and stops the movement of adjacent teeth. Veneers can also help prevent further damage or tooth loss, in addition to improving their appearance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>2. Why Do People See a Cosmetic Dentist?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Cosmetic dentists treat all kinds of people when the appearance of their teeth or smile is crucial to their work, life, or self-esteem. Through cosmetic dentistry procedures, anyone with damaged teeth, discoloration, gaps, or missing or crooked teeth can find solutions.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>3. How Can a Broken Tooth Be Saved?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Cosmetic dentistry techniques can fix a broken tooth in a variety of ways, such as dental bonding for minor cracks or chips. Veneers can mask a chip or crack on the outer surface of a tooth, or you may require a crown to replace the damaged part of the tooth and protect the root.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\r\n<h4><strong>4. What are the Long-term Costs and Longevity of the Treatment?</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Before you commit to any particular procedure, be sure to factor in the financial costs. A good prosthodontist will offer expert advice and recommendations for a course of action that best suits your budget. So that you can get a good idea of the overall cost of your dental investment, ask about long-term care costs that may come with repeated visits and treatment longevity.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '2022-07-18 09:24:07.756698');
